[Term]
id: MONDO:0001347
name: facioscapulohumeral muscular dystrophy
def: "An autosomal dominant disorder affecting the skeletal muscles of the face, scapula, and upper arm. Patients present with muscle weakness in these anatomic areas. The muscle weakness eventually spreads to other skeletal muscles as well." [NCIT:C84704]
