[Term]
id: MONDO:0008050
name: MYH7-related skeletal myopathy
def: "A rare autosomal dominant distal myopathy characterized by preferential weakness of the great toe, ankle dorsiflexor, finger extensor and neck flexor. Progression is slow with variations in age of onset, severity, weakness, cardiac, and respiratory involvement." [Orphanet:59135]
