[Term]
id: MONDO:0010006
name: Sandhoff disease
def: "A lysosomal disorder from the GM2 gangliosidosis family, caused by biallelic pathogenic variants in the HEXB gene, characterized by GM2 ganglioside accumulation in the nervous system and progressive central nervous system degeneration." [https://clinicalgenome.org/affiliation/40110/, Orphanet:796]
