[Term]
id: MONDO:0013390
name: autosomal recessive limb-girdle muscular dystrophy type 2Q
def: "A form of limb-girdle muscular dystrophy characterized by proximal muscle weakness presenting in early childhood (with occasional falls and difficulties in climbing stairs) and a progressive course resulting in loss of ambulation in early adulthood. Muscle atrophy and multiple contractures have also been reported in rare cases." [Orphanet:254361]
