[Term]
id: MONDO:0976133
name: myopathy, myofibrillar, 13, with rimmed vacuoles
def: "A rare genetic neuromuscular disease caused by a mutation in HSPB8 gene, characterized by length-dependent axonal motor neuropathy predominantly affecting the lower limbs, in combination with a myopathy with morphological features of myofibrillar myopathy with aggregates and rimmed vacuoles." [Orphanet:476093]
comment: Age of onset is typically in the second to third decade of life. Patients present with slowly progressive muscle weakness and atrophy initially affecting the distal lower limbs and later progressing to involve proximal limbs and also truncal muscles. There is no involvement of respiratory and cardiac muscles.
synonym: "autosomal dominant distal axonal motor neuropathy-myofibrillar myopathy syndrome" EXACT [MONDO:0018773]
synonym: "HSPB8-associated autosomal dominant rimmed vacuolar myopathy" EXACT [PMID:31403083]
synonym: "HSPB8-related autosomal dominant distal axonal motor neuropathy-myofibrillar myopathy syndrome" EXACT [Orphanet:476093]
synonym: "limb-girdle rimmed vacuolar myopathy" EXACT [PMID:32165108]
synonym: "MFM13" EXACT ABBREVIATION [Orphanet:476093]
synonym: "rimmed vacuoles myopathy" EXACT [Orphanet:476093]
